# Phase 0 Setup Guide — Foundations

**Scope:** Config Registry · Authorization Gate · Audit Log v2 with Run IDs · Governance Prompt v7
**Time required:** ~2–3 hours
**Prerequisite:** the working forecasting agent (Tool 6 v4.1) as of 2026-07-01
**Golden rule:** do not start a step until the previous step's verification passes.

---

## Before you start — two concepts in plain English

**Configuration vs. code.** Today, values like "which properties exist" live inside JavaScript. Phase 0 moves them into a Google Sheet. A sheet can be edited by anyone on the team without touching n8n, it has built-in edit history, and at migration time it converts 1:1 into SharePoint Lists. This single pattern — *config in tables, logic in code* — is the backbone of Power Automate portability.

**Run ID.** A run ID is a unique serial number stamped on every forecast run (it looks like `3f8a1c2e-...`). Every audit row, every workbook, every answer carries it. When someone asks "where did this number come from?" three months from now, the run ID is how you answer in 30 seconds instead of never.

