## STEP 5 — End-to-End Verification (Phase 0 exit criteria)

Run all five; all must pass:

| # | Test | Pass condition |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Normal forecast (prop01) | Workbook correct, reply has source tags + Run ID, one audit row |
| 2 | Unauthorized user (Users.active=FALSE, then back) | Denial message; zero LLM calls in execution log |
| 3 | Trap question (estimate request) | Declines to invent a number |
| 4 | Audit trace | Run ID in chat reply == run_id of newest sheet row |
| 5 | Regression | Workbook numbers identical to a pre-Phase-0 run for the same inputs |

**Phase 0 is complete when all five pass.** Next phase: **Phase 1 — Intent Router + Business Rules Engine**, which moves the scenario percentages out of `compute-financials-v4.js` into config (this is why the Config Registry came first) and adds the Haiku-class router (this is why roles already list allowed intents).

